The paper deals with lower bounds on the minimum distance of codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of spectral analysis and eigenvalues of polynomial matrices suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper may also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of spectral analysis.
